# Production env for the full docker-compose.yml stack.
# Copy to `.env` next to docker-compose.yml on the host that runs it
# (build machine AND the VPS). Compose auto-loads `.env`.
#
#   cp .env.prod.example .env   &&   edit
#
# (For LOCAL DEV use .env.example → apps/web/.env.local instead; this file is
#  only for the containerized prod stack.)

# ── Mandatory secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HMAC for session cookies. >=32 chars.  openssl rand -base64 48
SESSION_SECRET=
# AES-256 vault key. 32 random bytes, base64.  openssl rand -base64 32
MANTLE_MASTER_KEY=
# OPTIONAL. UUID of your single auth.users row. Leave BLANK for a fresh install
# (the runtime auto-resolves the sole user; create your account in the web app on
# first visit). Set it only when importing existing data — it must match the user
# in that data — or to disambiguate a multi-DB setup.
#   (from dev:  docker exec mantle_dev_pg psql -U postgres -d postgres -tA -c "select id from auth.users limit 1")
ALLOWED_USER_ID=

# ── Postgres / object storage ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=change-me
S3_ACCESS_KEY=minio
S3_SECRET_KEY=change-me-too

# ── Public origin (share links, email links, agent tools) ─────────────────────
MANTLE_PUBLIC_URL=https://mantle.example.com

# ── Caddy front door (automatic HTTPS) ────────────────────────────────────────
# The address Caddy serves. A hostname → Caddy gets a Let's Encrypt cert
# automatically (point a DNS A record at the VPS + open ports 80/443 first).
# Leave as :80 for local HTTP testing without a domain.
MANTLE_SITE_ADDRESS=mantle.example.com

# ── Persistent data location (host bind-mount root) ───────────────────────────
# postgres, minio, and files all live under here. Back it up; rsync it to move
# files between machines. (Move the DB itself via scripts/db-dump.sh, not by
# copying postgres/.)  Absolute path recommended on the VPS, e.g. /opt/mantle/data
MANTLE_DATA_DIR=./data

# ── Docker Hub image (pull, or build → push → pull) ───────────────────────
# Every service runs from ONE image: <namespace>/mantle:<tag>. The default
# (titanwest) is the official published image — most installs never change it.
# Self-builders: set your own Docker Hub user/org (scripts/docker-build-push.sh
# reads it too). Pin MANTLE_IMAGE_TAG to a release (e.g. v0.20.66) for
# reproducible updates; `latest` tracks the newest release.
MANTLE_IMAGE_NAMESPACE=titanwest
MANTLE_IMAGE_TAG=latest
# Third-party images are PINNED in docker-compose.yml (not :latest) so the in-app
# update path can't pull a breaking upstream release mid-update. Uncomment to
# move a pin without editing compose; defaults are the compose-pinned tags.
# MINIO_IMAGE_TAG=RELEASE.2025-09-07T16-13-09Z
# MC_IMAGE_TAG=RELEASE.2025-08-13T08-35-41Z
# OLLAMA_IMAGE_TAG=0.32.1

# ── In-app updater (Settings → Updates) ───────────────────────────────────────
# HOST-absolute path of THIS directory (the one holding docker-compose.yml + this
# .env). The updater sidecar bind-mounts it and runs `docker compose` against it
# to apply updates from the UI. REQUIRED for in-app updates: if it's blank the
# updater parks "unconfigured" and Settings → Updates hangs on "Working…" forever
# (and the bind-mount falls back to the wrong path). install.sh writes this
# automatically; on a MANUAL install set it by hand to this directory:
#   MANTLE_STACK_DIR=$(pwd -P)
MANTLE_STACK_DIR=

# ── Local embedder (bundled Ollama) — OPT-IN, off by default ──────────────────
# Embedding is online by default (set up in onboarding: text-embedding-3-large,
# 768-dim). The local embedder is for advanced / air-gapped setups. It does NOT
# run unless you enable the profile:
#   docker compose --profile local-embedder up -d
# then point the brain at it in Settings → Embedding (provider "local"). Tuning:
# Set OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=-1 to keep the embedder resident.
# OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=5m
# MANTLE_EMBEDDING_PULL_MODEL=embeddinggemma
#
# On a small CPU-only box, large files can time out mid-embed (many chunks per
# file × slow inference). If you see extractor "operation aborted due to timeout"
# errors on big files, tune these down — serialize extraction so jobs don't
# contend for cores, and shrink each embed request so it clears the window:
# EXTRACT_CONCURRENCY=1
# MANTLE_LOCAL_EMBED_BATCH=8
# MANTLE_LOCAL_EMBED_TIMEOUT_MS=120000   # raise (ms) for very slow hardware
# MANTLE_EXTRACT_EXPIRE_MIN=60           # max minutes a single extraction may run
#                                        # before pg-boss expires+retries the job.
#                                        # Default 60; raise if big docs still
#                                        # dead-letter mid-embed on very slow CPUs.
# The real fix for bulky-document workloads is a faster embedder (more vCPU, a
# GPU, or a remote EmbeddingGemma route). Full guide: docs/embeddings.md
# ("Throughput on a CPU-only box").

# ── Tailscale (optional — `docker compose --profile tailnet up -d`) ───────────
# Reach models on a box you own behind NAT. Generate an auth key in the TS admin
# console. See docs/tailscale.md.
# TS_AUTHKEY=
# TS_HOSTNAME=mantle-vps

# ── Live turn streaming (ON by default) ──────────────────────────────────────
# The chat "thinking" trail + live reply typing stream over SSE out of the box.
# Per-BRAIN control lives in the UI: Settings → Profile → "Live thinking &
# streaming" (a runtime preference). These env vars are a deploy-level OFF
# override — uncomment to force the whole box dark regardless of the profile.
# MANTLE_TURN_STREAMING=0          # master: SSE route + non-blocking POST + buffer
# MANTLE_TURN_NARRATION=0          # the per-step LLM "thinking" phrases (has a cost)
# MANTLE_TURN_TOKENS=0             # live reply token typing

# ── Runner queues (OFF by default — pre-release) ─────────────────────────────
# Durable background runs (docs/runs.md): the responder can delegate multi-step
# jobs to a queued plan of tool calls + worker-agent steps with automatic
# audits, tracked at /debug/runs. Uncomment to enable on this brain; the
# worker_runs container idles healthy while unset. Also grant the `runs` tool
# group to your persona (Settings → Tool groups) so the responder sees the
# run_plan/run_state/run_audit tools.
# MANTLE_RUNS=1
#
# How many worker-agent steps of ONE run may execute concurrently (each is a
# whole LLM agent turn). Default 3 — protects small boxes from wide fan-outs.
# MANTLE_RUNS_WORKER_CONCURRENCY=3

# ── Optional / advanced (sane defaults; uncomment only if you need them) ──────
# Mobile/companion + detached (Electron) clients: comma-separated origins allowed
# to call the API cross-origin. Empty = same-origin only (the web app works as-is).
# MANTLE_API_CORS_ORIGINS=https://app.example.com,capacitor://localhost
#
# Number of trusted reverse-proxy hops in front of the app, for correct client-IP
# rate-limiting. Default 1 is right behind the bundled Caddy; raise if you add
# another proxy layer (e.g. Cloudflare → your LB → Caddy).
# MANTLE_TRUSTED_PROXIES=1
#
# Push notifications: the blind E2E relay the companion app polls. Defaults to the
# hosted relay; set this only if you run your own (see ~/Projects/mantle-push).
# MANTLE_PUSH_RELAY_URL=https://push.example.com
#
# Microsoft 365 ingest (SharePoint / OneDrive / Outlook). Optional — the primary
# path is the in-app Settings → Integrations config row; these are an env fallback.
# Leave blank to keep the Microsoft worker idle (it no-ops without config).
# MS_CLIENT_ID=
# MS_CLIENT_SECRET=
# MS_TENANT=common
# MS_REDIRECT_URI=https://mantle.example.com/api/integrations/microsoft/callback
